<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1890,2036]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[151,280,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Tentacular membrane expanded, trilobed, wide; eyespots and lateral lappets absent; small midventral shields; six to 12 thoracic segments; notopodia from segment 3, notochaetae smooth, hirsute or pinnate; abdominal notopodia and notochaetae absent; thoracic and abdominal neuropodia and neurochaeta absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,152,338]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis box="[198,310,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks:</emphasis>
Only one species has been described for the Western Atlantic Ocean, 
<taxonomicName authority="Webster, 1879" authorityName="Webster" authorityYear="1879" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Lysilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[1181,1323,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lysilla alba</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Webster, H. E." pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="101 - 128" refId="ref65013" refString="Webster, H. E. (1879) Annelida Chaetopoda of New Jersey. Annual Report of New York State Museum of Natural Science, 32, 101 - 128." type="journal article" year="1879">Webster, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingRegion box="[296,395,192,218]" country="United States of America" name="Virginia" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Virginia</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Londono-Mesa, M. H. &amp; Carrera-Parra, L. F." box="[409,900,192,218]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref63133" refString="Londono-Mesa, M. H. &amp; Carrera-Parra, L. F. (2005) Terebellidae (Polychaeta) from the Mexican Caribbean with description of four new species. Zootaxa, 1057, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="2005">Londoño-Mesa and Carrera-Parra (2005)</bibRefCitation>
reported an undescribed species, 
<taxonomicName box="[1313,1436,192,218]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Lysilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1313,1392,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lysilla</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
from the Mexican 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[372,496,232,258]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="18" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
; nevertheless, this species was not named because it was only 
<specimenCount box="[1243,1405,232,258]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
in poor condition. Herein, I report an additional specimen in better condition; it is named as 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[1230,1393,272,297]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Lysilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caribe" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1230,1393,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lysilla caribe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
being the only species described from the Grand 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[782,902,312,338]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="18" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
region.
</paragraph>
